    "description": "P-channel JFET common-source (polarity-inverted topology): Vdd at source = +10V; drain to ground via Rd=10kOhm; gate at +7V. With default PJFET (VTO=+2V), polarity*(Vg-Vs) = -1*(7-10) = +3V > VTO=+2 -> conducting.",
